13 Sec. 412. (1) The legislature finds that the availability of
14 nonalcoholic beverages, including nonalcoholic beer at tasting
15 rooms, promotes public health and safety when done through a
16 regulated structure that minimizes minor access to nonalcoholic
17 beer.
18 (2) The legislature further finds that the 3-tier distribution
19 system remains the most effective balance of increasing competition
20 and variety and access to market against public health and safety.
21 The ability of a wholesaler to sell nonalcoholic products to a
22 brewer operating a tasting room under this section must not be used
23 to undermine the 3-tier distribution system.
24 (3) Notwithstanding anything in this act to the contrary, a
25 wholesaler may sell beer as defined in section 105(8)(b) to a
26 brewer or micro brewer to sell at the brewer's or micro brewer's
27 approved tasting room for consumption on or off the licensed
28 premises.
29 (4) A brewer or micro brewer that purchases beer as defined in
DAW S01868'25 (S-2) zh0gju

