18 (3) A wholesaler or manufacturer may give samples of beer or
19 wine to an employee of the wholesaler if all of the following
20 conditions are met:
21 (a) The sampling is for the purpose of educating the employee
22 regarding the beer or wine.
23 (b) The employee is at least 21 years of age.
24 (c) The sampling takes place on the licensed premises of the
25 wholesaler.
26 (4) A micro brewer or a brewer may give samples of beer to an
27 employee of another brewer or micro brewer if all of the following
28 conditions are met:
29 (a) The sampling is for the purpose of research or of
DAW S01868'25 (S-2) zh0gju

20
1 educating the employee regarding the beer.
2 (b) The employee is at least 21 years of age.
3 (c) The sampling takes place on the licensed premises of the
4 other micro brewer or the other brewer.
5 (5) (4) A vendor shall not sell an alcoholic liquor to an
6 individual in an intoxicated condition.
7 (6) (5) Evidence of any breathalyzer or blood alcohol test
8 results obtained in a licensed establishment, or on property
9 adjacent to the licensed premises and under the control or
10 ownership of the licensee, is not admissible to prove a violation
11 of this section, section 707(1), (2), (3), or (4), or section
12 801(1). To establish a violation of this section, section 707(1),
13 (2), (3), or (4), or section 801(1), the individual's intoxicated
14 condition at the time of the sale or consumption of alcohol must be
15 proven by direct observation by law enforcement or commission
16 enforcement personnel or through other admissible witness
17 statements or corroborating evidence obtained as part of the
18 standard investigation other than breathalyzer or blood alcohol
19 test results.
20 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
21 unless Senate Bill No. 513 of the 103rd Legislature is enacted into
22 law.
